Sentinel Health

Sentinel Health is an AI-based video analysis system that detects human falls, unsafe postures, emotions, and aggressive actions from uploaded videos or webcam feeds using deep learning models.

Features

Secure login dashboard

Upload and analyze videos

Fall detection

Unsafe pose detection

Facial emotion recognition

Action & aggression detection

Visual and audio alerts for critical events

Models Used

YOLOv8 – Person detection

YOLOv8-Pose – Pose estimation

FER – Emotion recognition

SlowFast R50 – Aggressive action detection

Tech Stack

Python, Flask

OpenCV, NumPy

HTML, CSS, JavaScript

MongoDB (GridFS)

PyTorch

How to Run
1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/sentinel-health.git
cd sentinel-health

2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv


Activate:

Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

Linux/Mac: source venv/bin/activate

3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run the app
python app.py


Open browser:

http://127.0.0.1:5000
